Day of Sun Commemorated Abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 7 (KCNA) -- Functions took place in different countries on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.
 A commemorative meeting was held at the building of the Moscow City Committee of the Communist Party of the Russian Federation on April 2. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the progressives of the world are significantly commemorating the birth anniversary of Kim Il Sung, the great leader of the Korean people and the most distinguished statesman in the 20th century, speakers said, noting that he dedicated all his life to the victory of the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The most precious feat performed by him on behalf of humankind is that he fathered the immortal Juche idea, they said, stressing that it is an idea centered on the popular masses which the communist parties of all the countries should take as guidelines. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They continued: What is the most brilliant of his immortal feats is that he successfully settled the issue of carrying forward the cause of the Korean revolution. The Korean people are fully demonstrating the might of socialist Korea under the tested and wise guidance of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Commemorative meetings, round-table talks, film shows, photo and book exhibitions, art performances and national Taekwon-dochampionships were held in Patapo County, Lambayeque Province of Peru, the La Industria Newspaper Office of Peru, the Rural Community of Raburuwang District, Ayuthaya Province of Thailand, by the Egyptian folk dance troupe, the Uganda-DPRK Friendship Association, the Secretariat of the Pan-African Movement in Uganda and the Bulgarian Taekwon-do Federation from March 20 to 30. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "To Hold the Fatherly Leader in High Esteem", "The Fatherly Leader Is Together with Anti-Japanese Revolutionary Fighters" and other Korean films were screened at the film shows. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting held in Thailand.

Suppression of Political Activities in S. Korea under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 7 (KCNA) -- The south Korean Federation of University Student Councils (Hanchongryon) reportedly issued a statement on April 3 denouncing the police authorities for cracking down on the political activities of progressive movement organizations.
 Recalling that the police authorities are cracking down on members of the national trade union of civil servants who held a press conference supporting the Democratic Workers' Party and on members of the leadership of the National Teachers Union (Jongyojo) who published a declaration on the situation for nullifying the "impeachment" after issuing warrants of arrest of them, the statement said that the present "law on election" is wantonly encroaching upon the freedom of speech, press, assembly, association and expression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hanchongryon will in the future lay bare the injustice of the law and actively support the struggle of the national trade union of civil servants and Jongyojo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It will make every possible effort to build a society where free political activities of all the democratic, civic and public organizations and the just political expression of the people are ensured and liquidate the corrupt forces calling for "impeachment" in the forthcoming "general election".

Celebration Meetings Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 7 (KCNA) -- Celebration meetings of workers and members of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea (GFTUK) and the Union of Agricultural Workers of Korea (UAWK) were held separately on April 6 on the occasion of the 11th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK.
 Present there were Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, leading officials of working people's organizations and workers, members of the GFTUK and agricultural workers in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ryom Sun Gil, chairman of the Central Committee of the GFTUK, and Sung Sang Sop, chairman of the Central Committee of the UAWK, made reports at the meetings, which were followed by speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporters and speakers said that the election of Kim Jong Il to the highest post of the Korean revolution provided a sure guarantee for firmly defending the socialist cause of Juche and successfully accomplishing it and is bringing earlier a bright future of the country of Juche when it will throw its rays over the world as a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They stressed the need for the officials and members of the working people's organizations to devotedly defend Kim Jong Il and firmly prepare themselves to be the revolutionary comrades of Songun sharing their destiny with him to the last, taking it as the primary maxim in their life and struggle to devotedly defend the headquarters of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A commemorative poem "He is our chairman of the National Defence Commission" was recited at the celebration meeting of the workers and members of the GFTUK.

Authorities' Crackdown Condemned in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 7 (KCNA) -- The Headquarters of the Movement for the General Election reportedly made public a statement on April 3, condemning the south Korean authorities for their reckless crackdown on trade unions.
 The statement said that the authorities described the declaration on the situation for nullification of the impeachment and the declaration of support to the Democratic Workers' Party announced by the National Teachers Union and the national trade union of civil servants as the action of negating law and order and suppressed the chairmen of the unions on April 2, while blocking the Myongdong cultural festive for the defence of democracy which was scheduled to be held at Myongdong Cathedral. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The election management committee and the police resort to suppression on the pretext of fair election, the statement said, denouncing this as an encroachment on the right to freedom of the people under the fair-seeming signboard. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The declaration on the situation and the declaration of support are part of people's just right to the free expression of political will and the candlelight rally was also an eruption of people's resentment flailing the conservative forces' political coup, the statement said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It demanded that the election management committee and the police stop the eccentric suppression and provide a strict standard enough to guarantee a substantially fair election.

Jong Sun Dok Remembered 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 7 (KCNA) -- A memorial service for martyr Jong Sun Dok, an unconverted long-term prisoner of south Korea, was held in Pyongyang on April 6 under the sponsorship of the Korean Measure Committee for Rescuing Unconverted Long-term Prisoners in south Korea.
 Jong shed blood in the fight for national reunification as a brave woman guerrilla. She died of a long illness caused by long prison life and savage torture in south Korea on April 1 before seeing the day of reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hung in the venue of the memorial service was her portrait framed with a black ribbon. Placed before it were wreaths in the name of the Secretariat of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland, the Korean Measure Committee for Rescuing Unconverted Long-term Prisoners in south Korea, the unconverted long-term prisoners, the National Reconciliation Council, the North Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification and the North Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its participants observed a moment's silence in memory of Jong who devoted her whole life to the cause of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mun Jae Chol, chairman of the Korean Measure Committee for Rescuing Unconverted Long-term Prisoners in south Korea, and Kim Tong Gi, an unconverted long-term prisoner, made memorial addresses at the service. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A memorial poem was recited there.

DPRK Will Answer with Super-Tough Measure
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 7 (KCNA) -- The United States is now getting over-heated in its attempts to stifle the DPRK by military force, openly revealing its bandit-like nature. The DPRK will answer this with a super-tough measure.
 Minju Joson declares this in a commentary today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The news analyst says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 While intensifying anti-DPRK moves on the Korean peninsula, the United States is setting afloat rumors that it is gaining military "supremacy" over the DPRK so that the latter may not take a tough stand. If we follow the U.S. logic, the responsibility for the strained situation on the Korean Peninsula rests with the DPRK taking a tough stand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The gangster logic of the United States can never go down with us, even if it might be acceptable to anyone else. What is clear is that the U.S. does not seek dialogue with the DPRK but is trying to disarm it and stifle it by military force at any cost. This invariable scheme of the U.S. compels the DPRK to take a counter measure for putting fresh muscles into its military deterrent force to defend its sovereignty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK's tough measure against the U.S. is an entirely just one allowed by the self-defensive option of a sovereign state. No one can take issue with it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On this occasion the DPRK advises the U.S. once again to behave with discretion, seeing who is its adversary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Should the U.S. persist in its attempts to stifle the DPRK by military force, ignoring this warning, it would find itself fully to blame for all the unforeseeable consequences to be entailed by them. It would be too late, however bitterly it may repent of this then.

Vigilance against Japan's Reinvasion Moves Urged
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 7 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today in a signed commentary calls for guard against the reinvasion moves of Japan with regard to the very ominous military measures taken by it jointly with the United States to stifle the DPRK.
 The commentary says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The military moves of the U.S. and Japan targeted at the DPRK have become noticeably intensified. A typical example is the computer-aided U.S.-Japan mock joint war game code-named "Yamasakura-45" biggest ever in history which was staged recently in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The U.S. and Japan are planning to stage more than 10 joint military exercises of all arms of the three services and 3 to 5 large-scale joint military rehearsals of the three services this year. These are very ill-boding military steps aimed to stifle the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What merits special attention here is that Japan, instigated by the U.S., is working to carry into practice at any cost its wild designs to turn itself into a military power and stage a comeback to Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is abusing the nuclear issue of the Korean peninsula as a lever for realizing its wild ambition to become a military power and stage a comeback to Korea, while creating an atmosphere of military pressure upon the DPRK and rendering the situation strained through joint war games with the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;      
 Now Japan is bursting into limelight as a dangerous aggressive force and a war-seeking state and fully assuming the aggressive, brigandish and bellicose nature of "the Great Empire of Japan" which ran mad in the conquest of Asia and the world in the past. If Japan's moves for militarization and overseas aggression are allowed, it will result in bringing back the hurricane of war of Japan which swept the Asia-Pacific region in the last century. Its war hurricane in the 21st century will bring more disastrous consequences than that in the 20th century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 War and disasters should be prevented. The people of the world aspiring after independence and peace should clearly see the aggressive colors of Japan and its danger and vigorously turn out in the joint action to halt and frustrate its moves of militarization and overseas aggression.

Postage Stamps Issued in Commemoration of Day of Sun
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 7 (KCNA) -- The Korea Stamp Corporation has issued stamps -- a souvenir sheet and a postage stamp - in commemoration of the Day of the Sun (April 15).
 Printed on the upper part of the souvenir sheet are words "In commemoration of the birth anniversary of the great leader Comrade Kim Il Sung" and "Juche 1 (1912) - Juche 93 (2004)". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also seen in the sheet is a picture of President Kim Il Sung with a bright smile, framed with blossoms of magnolia, the national flower. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The stamp carries the words "In commemoration of the birth anniversary of the great leader Comrade Kim Il Sung. Juche 1 (1912) -Juche 93 (2004)" and, below them, shows his native home in Mangyongdae. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The prices of the stamps are 120 and 3 won respectively.

World Day of Health Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 7 (KCNA) -- April 7 is the "World Day of Health".
 On this day a function on the subject of "Safety on Roads" was held at the March 1 Bus Station of the Pyongyang Passenger Transport Complex today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Choe Chang Sik, vice-minister of Public Health, made an opening speech to be followed by a congratulatory speech by Umesh Gupta, official of the office of the WHO here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling the foundation of the WHO on April 7, 1948, speakers said that a universal free health care system was established and laws and regulations were instituted to firmly protect the people's health in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then followed a lecture on guaranteeing road safety and a function for pasting words "Safe Run" on buses.
